=== Running the Repertoire Faceting Demo

Rails 3 recommendation is to use database-specific schema dump and seeding files
unless your application is explicitly cross-database.

$ bundle install
$ rake db:faceting:build                 { sudo will prompt your password }
$ rake db:seeds:generate

The file db/development_structure.sql represents the current database schema, 
after all migrations have run (just like schema.db).  Source it and the seed 
data:

$ rake db:create
$ (cat db/*.sql data/*.sql) | psql -Upostgres repertoire_testing

And add the facet indices and run:

$ rake reindex
$ bundle exec rails s                    { see http://localhost:3000/nobelists }
